# Hikamp Rules

## General
- Read relevant files before making changes.
- Never invent APIs, JSON/XML fields, database columns, or function names.
- If information is missing, ask instead of guessing.
- Make the smallest possible change.
- Do not refactor unrelated code.

## Hikvision
- Use only official Hikvision documentation in /docs.
- Never modify payloads without verifying against documentation.
- For HTTP 400, inspect the outgoing request before changing logic.

## Go
- Use json.Marshal/json.NewEncoder.
- Never ignore errors.
- Reuse existing code when possible.

## Database
- Verify schema before changing SQL.
- Keep SELECT and Scan() order identical.

## Frontend
- Preserve HTMX and Alpine.js behavior.